reviews.review: Loved it! Can't wait to go see it again and again

I'm not sure what movie the negative reviewers saw, but it wasn't the same one I saw! Do yourself a favour, go to the theatre, sit back, and enjoy a great Star Wars movie! best one of the new trilogy, by far!

It's not the best film, it feels rushed at parts and like there was too much they had to stuff into it. However, it's a great and fitting ending to the saga. It felt right and it brought some tears to my eyes. As a super star wars nerd, I loved it.

Loved it - if you love the Star Wars saga and all the things that made it great when you were young, it is everything you will want to see in a wrap-up.  Directing is so much better than the last one.

It was okay still was looking for something more than advertised.... Just didn't think the woman role of saving the day was the way to go, by far i'm not commenting as sexism but just think it needed to be more of a ruff ending.

I felt it was the best of the recent trilogy films. JJ Abrams salvaged the trilogy as best he could and he returned to honoring the Star Wars canon. It was a decent film that could have been better if only one director had had creative control over the last 3 films. If only it had Darth Vader....
So good. The graphics and everything. The storyline was awesome too. Must see movie with your family.

I really think that if you didn't enjoy this movie, laugh at times, feel nostalgic at others and cry more than once then you really don't understand what a Star Wars movie was.  Was it a mess in places? Sure. Was it a perfect film? Of course not.  Was it everything to everybody? Hardly. But what movie is? It was an entertaining, beautifully shot, exhilarating ride that wrapped up most of the hanging questions and sent off the Skywalker saga in style.

I can't separate myself from the work and love that George Lucas put into the lore and history of his modern myth. Though, this movie is more of a middle finger to Rian Johnson's The Last Jedi than a love letter to the original trilogies, I found it lazy and schizophrenic at the same time. The visuals were amazing, but had the originality of the Cleveland Browns helmet redesign. There was not a story less convoluted in the entirety of the series. Normies will slide through this like prunes through a goose, but real fans will see some glaring problems.

The only Star I can give here is for the sound track... 

I have never seen a something so treasured by many to be so destroyed. 
You can clearly see JJ fighting for the last word in this series. This feels like it was more  of a sequel to the first movie than a third movie. Not to mention this movie clearly alienates most of the original cast. I feel a lot of characters suffered in this contest of Directors and you can see that it has hurt the series in a terrible way. 

I did my best not to point out spoilers, but this movie creates so much confusion its ridiculous.
